cc: Marc Dionne <marc.dionne@auristor.com>
cc: Simon Horman <horms@kernel.org>
cc: Willy Tarreau <w@1wt.eu>
cc: linux-afs@lists.infradead.org
cc: stable@kernel.org
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20260408121252.2249051-13-dhowells@redhat.com
Signed-off-by: Jakub Kicinski <kuba@kernel.org>

CVE-2026-31636
(cherry picked from commit 3e3138007887504ee9206d0bfb5acb062c600025)
Assisted-by: kybele:claude-opus-4.8
Signed-off-by: Cengiz Can <cengiz.can@canonical.com>
Acked-by: Hui Wang <hui.wang@canonical.com>
Acked-by: Jian Hui Lee <jianhui.lee@canonical.com>
Signed-off-by: Stefan Bader <stefan.bader@canonical.com>
---
 net/rxrpc/rxgk.c | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/net/rxrpc/rxgk.c b/net/rxrpc/rxgk.c
index 4d2a262b14cec655e47f57e12271cce02391405f..cd16e8e275d24024350ca7bbe402cbb46d0327db 100644
--- a/net/rxrpc/rxgk.c
+++ b/net/rxrpc/rxgk.c
@@ -1164,7 +1164,8 @@ static int rxgk_verify_authenticator(struct rxrpc_connection *conn,
 	}
 
 	p = auth;
-	ret = rxgk_do_verify_authenticator(conn, krb5, skb, p, p + auth_len);
+	ret = rxgk_do_verify_authenticator(conn, krb5, skb, p,
+					   p + auth_len / sizeof(*p));
 error:
 	kfree(auth);
 	return ret;
